{
  "title": "Google Gemini AI",
  "content": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Google Gemini AI is an advanced model by Google DeepMind that understands language, reasons and works with text, images, audio and video making it highly versatile and context-aware.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Handles complex tasks and problem-solving.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Understands different types of inputs together.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"key-features\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Coding Features</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Gemini AI is packed with useful tools for coding workflows:</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Code Generation</strong></b><span>: Generate Python scripts, JavaScript functions, Java programs and more. Just describe what you need and receive ready-to-run code.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Code Explanation</strong></b><span>: Explain complex concepts such as recursion, async programming and algorithms making them easy to understand for beginners and experts alike.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><b><strong>Debugging Support</strong></b><span>: Quickly identifies errors like missing semicolons, logic flaws or syntax issues and provides suggestions to fix them.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><b><strong>Multimodal Input</strong></b><span>: Handles text and images to convert UI sketches into HTML/CSS or analyze screenshots for code improvements.</span></li><li value=\"5\"><b><strong>Real Time Insights</strong></b><span>: Stays updated with the latest libraries, frameworks and coding trends.</span></li><li value=\"6\"><b><strong>Context Aware Assistance</strong></b><span>: Tracks your project context for tailored suggestions without repeated explanations.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"performance-and-accuracy\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Performance and Reliability</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>It delivers strong performance in coding and problem-solving, providing fast and accurate results across different tasks. It competes with top AI models by maintaining high accuracy and efficiency.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>HumanEval (80\u201392%):</strong></b><span> Performs well in code generation and explanation.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>MMLU (80\u201391%):</strong></b><span> Handles advanced programming and reasoning questions.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><b><strong>GSM8K (86\u201394%):</strong></b><span> Solves math-based coding problems effectively.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"architecture\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Architecture</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Gemini AI is built on Google\u2019s cutting-edge infrastructure:</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Decoder-only\" height=\"559\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260324090208535998/Decoder-only.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260324090208535998/Decoder-only.webp 434w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260324090208535998/Decoder-only-100.webp 78w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260324090208535998/Decoder-only-200.webp 155w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260324090208535998/Decoder-only-300.webp 233w\" width=\"434\"/><figcaption>Decoder Only Architecture</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Transformer-Based Neural Network</strong></b><span>: Trained on billions of tokens from code repositories, documentation and web sources.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Massive Context Window</strong></b><span>: 1-million-token window allows handling of large codebases seamlessly.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><b><strong>Reinforcement Learning</strong></b><span>: Continuously improves accuracy through feedback loops.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><b><strong>High-Speed Processing</strong></b><span>: Powered by Google TPU clusters for lightning fast responses.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"training-methodology\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Training Approach</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>It is trained using a combination of real data, human feedback and advanced techniques to improve accuracy and reliability.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Human Feedback</strong></b><span>: Coders and engineers refined its conversational precision.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Synthetic Data</strong></b><span>: Simulated scenarios prepared it for uncommon coding challenges.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><b><strong>Diverse Sources</strong></b><span>: Trained on GitHub, Stack Overflow and tech blogs.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><b><strong>Bias Mitigation</strong></b><span>: Designed to provide fair and accurate coding suggestions.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"how-to-usegoogle-gemini-ai\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>How to use Gemini AI\u00a0</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Gemini AI is easy to use and provides a simple interface to perform various tasks like coding, writing and problem-solving.</span></p><h3 id=\"step-1-access-gemini-ai\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 1: Access Gemini AI</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Visit Website:</strong></b><span> Go to the official Gemini website.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Sign Up:</strong></b><span> Log in using your Google account.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><b><strong>Choose Plan:</strong></b><span> Use free access or select a paid plan.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><b><strong>Get Started:</strong></b><span> You\u2019ll be redirected to the Gemini home page and can start using it.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN\" height=\"439\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN.webp 900w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN-300.webp 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN-660.webp 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722125938123959/GEMINI-AI-SIGNIN-768.webp 768w\" width=\"900\"/><figcaption>Access Gemini AI</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"step2-enter-your-query-or-prompt-in-the-box\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 2: Enter Your Prompt in the Box</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>After signing in, you will see the Gemini home page with a prompt box at the bottom. You can either use sample questions or ask your own.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Use Suggestions: </strong></b><span>Try the sample questions shown above the prompt box.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Enter Prompt:</strong></b><span> Type your question in the  Enter a prompt here  box.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><b><strong>Voice Input:</strong></b><span> You can also use voice to give input.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><b><strong>Submit: </strong></b><span>Press Enter to send your prompt.</span></li><li value=\"5\"><b><strong>Get Response: </strong></b><span>Gemini analyzes your input and gives a relevant answer.</span></li><li value=\"6\"><b><strong>New Chat:</strong></b><span> Click  New Chat  to start a separate conversation.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"gemini-prompt\" height=\"443\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt.webp 900w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt-300.webp 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt-660.webp 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722142100054227/gemini-prompt-768.webp 768w\" width=\"900\"/><figcaption> Enter Your Query or Prompt in the Box</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"1-on-pixel-devices\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 3: Write a prompt</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Clearly describe your task, like  Sort an array in Python or Fix my HTML code. Mention the programming language and context for better results.</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"new-gemini-prompt\" height=\"137\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt.webp 900w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt-300.webp 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt-660.webp 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162040877408/new-gemini-prompt-768.webp 768w\" width=\"900\"/><figcaption>Write a prompt</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"step-4-select-a-mode\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 4: Specify Task Requirements</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Clearly specify what you want Gemini to do, such as generating code, debugging or explaining a concept. Adding details like programming language and constraints helps improve the output.</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"sort-an-array\" height=\"442\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162352664819/sort-an-array.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162352664819/sort-an-array.webp 544w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162352664819/sort-an-array-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162352664819/sort-an-array-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722162352664819/sort-an-array-300.webp 300w\" width=\"544\"/><figcaption>Select a Model</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"step-4-review-output\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 5: Review Output</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Gemini AI provides code or explanations. For example, ask for a webpage and it might return HTML/CSS with comments.</span></p><h3 id=\"step-5-refine-and-test\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 6: Refine and Test</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>If the output needs tweaks, adjust your prompt (e.g., Add error handling to this Python script). Test the code in a safe environment.</span></p><h3 id=\"step-6-apply-or-share\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 7: Apply or Share</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Copy the code into your project or share it via your preferred platform.</span></p><h2 id=\"use-cases\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Use Cases</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>It is versatile for various coding scenarios. Here are examples with prompts and outputs:</span></p><h3 id=\"debugging-code\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>1. Debugging Code</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Prompt</strong></b><span>: Find the error in this Python code: for i in range(5): print(i * )</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Output</strong></b><span>:</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"usecase-example\" height=\"346\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163000272041/usecase-example.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163000272041/usecase-example.webp 574w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163000272041/usecase-example-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163000272041/usecase-example-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163000272041/usecase-example-300.webp 300w\" width=\"574\"/><figcaption>Debugging Code</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"writing-functions\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>2. Writing Functions</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Prompt</strong></b><span>: Write a JavaScript function to validate an email</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Output</strong></b><span>:</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"writing\" height=\"456\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163559549056/writing.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163559549056/writing.webp 580w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163559549056/writing-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163559549056/writing-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163559549056/writing-300.webp 300w\" width=\"580\"/><figcaption>Writing Functions</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"learning-concepts\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>3. Learning Concepts</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Prompt</strong></b><span>: Explain how JavaScript closures work</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Output</strong></b><span>:</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"javascript\" height=\"152\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163915002763/javascript.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163915002763/javascript.webp 598w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163915002763/javascript-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163915002763/javascript-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250722163915002763/javascript-300.webp 300w\" width=\"598\"/><figcaption>Learning Concepts</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"building-apps\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>4. Building Apps</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Prompt: Generate a simple login page using HTML and CSS</span><br/><b><strong>Output:</strong></b></p>[GFGTABS]<gfg-tabs data-mode=\"light\" data-run-ide=\"false\">\n            <gfg-tab slot=\"tab\">HTML</gfg-tab>\n<gfg-panel slot=\"panel\" data-code-lang=\"html\" data-main-code-start=\"None\" data-main-code-end=\"None\">\n    <code class=\"language-html\"><div class=highlight><pre><span></span><span class=cp>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>html</span> <span class=na>lang</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;en&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>head</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>meta</span> <span class=na>charset</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;UTF-8&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>meta</span> <span class=na>name</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;viewport&quot;</span> <span class=na>content</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>title</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Simple Login<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>title</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>link</span> <span class=na>rel</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;stylesheet&quot;</span> <span class=na>href</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;style.css&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>head</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>body</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>div</span> <span class=na>class</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;login-container&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>h2</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Login<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>h2</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>form</span> <span class=na>action</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;#&quot;</span> <span class=na>method</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;POST&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>div</span> <span class=na>class</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;input-group&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>label</span> <span class=na>for</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;username&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Username<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>label</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>input</span> <span class=na>type</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;text&quot;</span> <span class=na>id</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;username&quot;</span> <span class=na>name</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;username&quot;</span> <span class=na>required</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>div</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>div</span> <span class=na>class</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;input-group&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>label</span> <span class=na>for</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;password&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Password<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>label</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>input</span> <span class=na>type</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;password&quot;</span> <span class=na>id</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;password&quot;</span> <span class=na>name</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;password&quot;</span> <span class=na>required</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>div</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>button</span> <span class=na>type</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;submit&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Login<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>button</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>div</span> <span class=na>class</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;links&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>a</span> <span class=na>href</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;#&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Forgot Password?<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>a</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;</span><span class=nt>a</span> <span class=na>href</span><span class=o>=</span><span class=s>&quot;#&quot;</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>Sign Up<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>a</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>div</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>form</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>div</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>body</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n<span class=p>&lt;/</span><span class=nt>html</span><span class=p>&gt;</span>\n</pre></div></code>\n</gfg-panel>\n            <gfg-tab slot=\"tab\">CSS</gfg-tab>\n<gfg-panel slot=\"panel\" data-code-lang=\"css\" data-main-code-start=\"None\" data-main-code-end=\"None\">\n    <code class=\"language-css\"><div class=highlight><pre><span></span><span class=nt>body</span><span class=w> </span><span class=p>{</span>\n<span class=w>    </span><span class=k>font-family</span><span class=p>:</span><span class=w> </span><span class=n>Arial</span><span class=p>,</span><span class=w> </span><span class=kc>sans-