mate repetitive tasks.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"advantages-of-google-gemini-ai\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Advantages </span></h2><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Handles text, code, images, audio and video for versatile assistance.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Provides accurate, context aware solutions and step by step explanations.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><span>Generates, debugs and explains code across multiple programming languages.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><span>Accesses latest libraries, trends and best practices to keep outputs current.</span></li><li value=\"5\"><span>Works across Google platforms, cloud APIs and Google Assistant.</span></li><li value=\"6\"><span>Remembers project context to offer tailored suggestions.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"limitations-of-google-gemini-ai\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Limitations</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Gemini AI is useful, but it still has some limitations that users should keep in mind.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>May struggle with less common programming languages or frameworks.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Very large or complex projects may not be fully understood.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><span>Image, video and UI to code features are still improving.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><span>Unclear instructions can lead to weaker results.</span></li><li value=\"5\"><span>Outputs should always be checked and tested before use.</span></li></ul>",
